To clear the page and create new data according to your needs, you can use React Navigation to navigate to the current page and reset the stack of the navigator.

Here's an example code snippet:

```javascript
import { StackActions } from '@react-navigation/native';

//In your component, use the following code to navigate and reset stack
navigation.dispatch(StackActions.replace('CurrentScreen', { data: newData }));

//Here, 'CurrentScreen' is the name of the current screen, and 'newData' is the data you want to pass to this screen.

```

This will replace the current screen with a new one and reset the entire stack of the navigator.
